{
  "text": "where m λ , k 1 , k 2 , C and X are observed instrumental magnitude, primary and secondary extinction coefficients, colour index and air mass, respectively. M λ , η λ , ζ λ are standard magnitude, atmospheric extinctioncorrected instrumental magnitude, transformation coefficient and photometric zero point, respectively. The other details of data reduction can be found in the papers of Akkaya et al. (2010) [CITATION_1] and Akkaya et al. (2015) [17]. Air-mass range and exposure times in each band during the observations are given in rows 5-10 of Table  1 . Figure 2 presents the finding chart Figure 3 . Its mean photometric errors are also listed in Table 2 . Our inspection of Figure  3 and Table 2 ",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "118578066"
